Name: Description
Poverty by Race/Ethnicity: Individuals living in households with incomes below the Federal Poverty Level (FPL) by racial/ethnic groups. Racial/ethnic groups are defined as follows: White = non-Latino White alone, Black = non-Latino Black alone, Asian = non-Latino Asian or Pacific Islander alone, Latino = Latino of any race.

Name: Source Notes
Poverty by Race/Ethnicity: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Public Use Microdata Sample File (2007-2018); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.
